fields.name: AcceptedAudiences
fields.description: The cluster's accepted audiences.

fields.name: AllowedFqdnList
fields.description: List of allowed FQDNs(Fully Qualified Domain Name) for egress from Cluster.

fields.name: AllowedIPRangeList
fields.description: The list of ips in the format of CIDR allowed to connect to the cluster.

fields.name: DataIngestionUri
fields.description: The cluster data ingestion URI.

fields.name: EnableAutoStop
fields.description: A boolean value that indicates if the cluster could be automatically stopped (due to lack of data or no activity for many days).

fields.name: EnableDiskEncryption
fields.description: A boolean value that indicates if the cluster's disks are encrypted.

fields.name: EnableDoubleEncryption
fields.description: A boolean value that indicates if double encryption is enabled.

fields.name: EnablePurge
fields.description: A boolean value that indicates if the purge operations are enabled.

fields.name: EnableStreamingIngest
fields.description: A boolean value that indicates if the streaming ingest is enabled.

fields.name: EngineType
fields.description: The engine type

fields.name: KeyVaultProperties
fields.description: KeyVault properties for the cluster encryption.

fields.name: LanguageExtensions
fields.description: List of the cluster's language extensions.

fields.name: MigrationCluster
fields.description: Properties of the peer cluster involved in a migration to/from this cluster.

fields.name: OptimizedAutoscale
fields.description: Optimized auto scale definition.

fields.name: PrivateEndpointConnections
fields.description: A list of private endpoint connections.

fields.name: ProvisioningState
fields.description: The provisioned state of the resource.

fields.name: PublicIPType
fields.description: Indicates what public IP type to create - IPv4 (default), or DualStack (both IPv4 and IPv6)

fields.name: PublicNetworkAccess
fields.description: Public network access to the cluster is enabled by default. When disabled, only private endpoint connection to the cluster is allowed

fields.name: RestrictOutboundNetworkAccess
fields.description: Whether or not to restrict outbound network access.  Value is optional but if passed in, must be 'Enabled' or 'Disabled'

fields.name: State
fields.description: The state of the resource.

fields.name: StateReason
fields.description: The reason for the cluster's current state.

fields.name: TrustedExternalTenants
fields.description: The cluster's external tenants.

fields.name: Uri
fields.description: The cluster URI.

fields.name: VirtualClusterGraduationProperties
fields.description: Virtual Cluster graduation properties

fields.name: VirtualNetworkConfiguration
fields.description: Virtual network definition.
